LEARNING IS FUN - Encourage creativity for STEM education which is the key factor to success in today's ever-changing environment. Fun and entertaining; perfect educational present for school age children that will never go out of style.

FUN FOR EVERYBODY - PTB240 encourages children and/or families to work together as a team to design the masterpiece structures and build the creations. Entertaining for single or multiple parties and feel the sense of achievement of building together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My opinion - BEST toy for a child on many different levels!
reviews.reviewText: My Husband and I babysit our 6 yr old Grandson and he has us wrapped around each of his little fingers. We have tried to find a building kit that would challenge him and keep his interest for more than a few minutes. The "PicassoTiles PTT136 136pcs Tubular Pipes & Spout" have been the answer. He LOVES these and has played with them every day for the last 2 months. He builds anything his imagination thinks of. The first thing he built was a diesel truck with dual smoke stacks and a flatbed. The pieces in this set have been very well planned. There hasn't been a single frustration because each piece was made for a child's imagination. He has built trumpets, lasers, harps, light sabers and much more. This was money very well spent. We are all of us very pleased with this set!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For kids who love to build—get these!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I have two 4 year olds who love to build and these have been a HIT! I’ve had to purchase more so they can add to their creations. I love that it’s open ended play and truly lets kids be creative. I will say, the horn piece is loud! But still so fun if you’re okay with that. My kids have loved everything we’ve ordered from Picasso, and these are no exception.

reviews.reviewText: I bought my grandson his first box when he was 18 months old and he is now 2 and I have him a bigger box and he plays with his plays with his picasso tiles all the time, he loves creating and making his own designs, especially cars and various air crafts. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cool but fragile
reviews.reviewText: This product is super fun to build with, but the little bristle parts do break off with any sort of rough play. We bought this product this year, and have seen the breaks multiple times, but the brand that target sells we have had for about 8 years and have never had the same issue. Still a great fun product if little children are not a concern.
